==Notes==
{{Portal box|Schools}}
{{cnote |a|By 1976, there were 16 different programs in 41 locations.{{sfn|Waldrip|1979|p=134}} The city was not successful in avoiding civil rights litigation. In 1974, the [[NAACP|National Association for the Advancement of Colored People]] filed suit demanding an end to segregated schooling in Cincinnati.<ref>{{Cite news| last = MacDonald | first = Sue | title = Cases of the Century | newspaper= Cincinnati Magazine | date = August 2001| page = 24 }}</ref> The settlement, reached in 1984, was, the court reported, "historic in allowing the school district charged with promoting or allowing unconstitutional desegregation to choose for itself the means to arrive at desegregation goals."<ref>{{cite court | litigants = [[Bronson v. Board of Educ. of City School Dist.]] | court = Dist. Court S. D. Ohio | vol = No. 1: | reporter = 74-cv-205 | date = 1991 | url=http://www.eric.ed.gov/ERICWebPortal/contentdelivery/servlet/ERICServlet?accno=ED339758}}</ref> Namely, the magnet school system, which was to operate under federal court supervision until 1991.}}
{{cnote |b|New York City had established the [[High School of Music and Art]] in 1936 and the [[High School of Performing Arts]] (for dance and drama) in 1948. They were combined in 1984 as the [[Fiorello H. LaGuardia High School of Music & Art and Performing Arts]].<ref>{{Cite news| title =La Guardia Reunion Celebrates Youth and the Arts| last =Bahrampour| first = Tara | newspaper = The New York Times | date = 2000<U+2013>06<U+2013>14 | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2000/06/14/nyregion/la-guardia-reunion-celebrates-youth-and-the-arts.html?pagewanted=all| accessdate = 2010<U+2013>01<U+2013>25 }}</ref>}}
{{cnote|c|As part of school tradition, graduating [[senior (education)|seniors]] walk outside around the building as part of the Class Day ceremony on their final day at SCPA to commemorate this daily trek.{{sfn | Student Handbook | 2007 | p = 2}}}}
{{cnote |d|Plans for Kunzel's original vision of an entire arts complex anchored by Music Hall were scaled back due to lack of funding.<ref>{{Cite news| title = SCPA Proposal Shrinks: Plan for Complex is Scaled Back | last = Griggs | first = France | newspaper = The Cincinnati Post | date = 2000<U+2013>03<U+2013>25 | url = http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-63450993.html | format = fee required | accessdate = 2010<U+2013>06<U+2013>07}}</ref>}}

